			&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; data-original-title=&quot;Reopen Ticket&quot; class=&quot;enable-tooltip btn btn-alt btn-danger reopen-btn&quot; id=&quot;reopen-btn&quot;&gt;Ticket Title&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;

Your JQuery should be,

    $(document).on(
		&quot;click&quot;,
		&quot;#reopen-btn&quot;,
		function (e){
			$(e.target).text(&#39;reopened : &#39; + $(e.target).text());
		}
	);


In your code you have try to bind a event to `&lt;a href&gt;` with its class name. But you have used `#reopen-btn` idendifier. `#` mark is used to identify an element with its `id`. So you need to add `id` attribute to your element or you need to identify it using `.reopen-btn`.

The other mistake is usage of `innerHTML`. With jQuery you can use `html` or `text` instead.

